is an English guitarist best known for his longtime role as lead guitarist of British rock band Jethro Tull, with whom he recorded and toured from 1968 until the band's initial dissolution in 2011.
Martin Barre was born in Kings Heath, Birmingham, England, on 17 November 1946.
